-- Saudi Arabia Has 54.3 Million Mobile-Phone Line Users, CITC Says
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-06-23T11:08:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-23/saudi-arabia-has-54-3-million-mobile-phone-line-users-citc-says.html
Saudi Arabia  had 54.3 million
mobile-phone subscribers at the end of the first quarter,
according to the kingdom’s telecommunications regulator.  The Arab world’s largest economy also had 14.2 million
internet users and 4.6 million fixed-line phone customers by the
end of March, the Communications and Information Technology
Commission said in an e-mailed  quarterly statement .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
